revision.text:
'''Elgin's Regiment of Fencible Infantry''' or '''Elgin's Fencible Highlanders''' was  raised in November 1794.{{sfn|McGuigan|2009}}

Major [[Thomas Bruce, 7th Earl of Elgin|Thomas, Earl of Elgin]], from the [[12th Foot]] was Colonel of this [[fencible]] regiment with the permanent army rank of Lieutenant-Colonel. John Hepburn Belches was appointed to be a Lieutenant-Colonel in the regiment and Patrick Tyler to be a Major.{{sfn|Chapman|1795|p=616}}

The regiment, was embodied in the Lowlands on 28 November 1794.{{sfn|McGuigan|2009}} It contained about 300 men from the [[Highlands of Scotland|Highlands]].{{sfn|Stewart|1822|p=296}} The regiment was posted to [[Ireland]] and was decommissioned on 15 October 1802.{{sfn|McGuigan|2009}}

